description:
Define a rich agent persona and customization system that gives each spawned agent role-specific tools, MCP servers, skills, and system prompts.

## Problem

Currently, agent profiles in agent-runtime-config.v2.json are minimal — just a system_prompt and model. All agents get the same capabilities regardless of their role. There's no way to:
- Scope which MCP tools an agent can access based on its role
- Add custom/project-specific MCP servers to agents
- Define reusable skills or behavioral directives per agent type
- Customize agents at the project level without changing global config
- Have agents communicate with each other through structured channels

## Vision

Transform the agent profile system into a full persona engine:

### Agent Profile Schema (extended)
```json
{
  "agents": {
    "em": {
      "role": "engineering-manager",
      "description": "Manages work queue, prioritizes tasks, allocates resources",
      "system_prompt": "You are the Engineering Manager agent...",
      "model": "gpt-5.3-codex",
      "mcp_servers": {
        "ao": {
          "source": "builtin",
          "tool_policy": {
            "mode": "allowlist",
            "patterns": ["ao.task.*", "ao.queue.*", "ao.workflow.*", "ao.daemon.*", "ao.agent.*"]
          }
        }
      },
      "skills": ["prioritization", "estimation", "dependency-analysis"],
      "capabilities": {
        "can_create_tasks": true,
        "can_assign_agents": true,
        "can_start_workflows": true,
        "can_modify_requirements": false,
        "can_write_code": false
      }
    },
    "po": {
      "role": "product-owner",
      "description": "Owns requirements, refines acceptance criteria, validates deliverables",
      "system_prompt": "You are the Product Owner agent...",
      "model": "gpt-5.3-codex",
      "mcp_servers": {
        "ao": {
          "source": "builtin",
          "tool_policy": {
            "mode": "allowlist",
            "patterns": ["ao.requirement.*", "ao.task.list", "ao.task.get", "ao.vision.*"]
          }
        }
      },
      "skills": ["requirement-refinement", "acceptance-criteria", "user-story-mapping"],
      "capabilities": {
        "can_create_tasks": false,
        "can_modify_requirements": true,
        "can_approve_deliverables": true,
        "can_write_code": false
      }
    },
    "swe": {
      "role": "software-engineer",
      "description": "Writes production code, runs tests, reviews implementations",
      "system_prompt": "You are the Software Engineer agent...",
      "model": "gpt-5.3-codex",
      "mcp_servers": {
        "ao": {
          "source": "builtin",
          "tool_policy": {
            "mode": "allowlist",
            "patterns": ["ao.task.*", "ao.workflow.*", "ao.output.*", "ao.agent.*"]
          }
        }
      },
      "skills": ["implementation", "testing", "code-review", "debugging"],
      "capabilities": {
        "can_write_code": true,
        "can_run_tests": true,
        "can_create_tasks": false,
        "can_modify_requirements": false
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Custom MCP Server Registration (per-project .ao/config.json)
```json
{
  "mcp_servers": {
    "browser-testing": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@playwright/mcp-server"],
      "env": {"BROWSER": "chromium"},
      "assign_to": ["swe"]
    },
    "design-system": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["./tools/design-mcp/index.js"],
      "assign_to": ["po", "swe"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Plugin/Skill System
Skills are reusable prompt fragments or behavioral directives:
```json
{
  "skills": {
    "prioritization": {
      "description": "Evaluate task priority using MoSCoW + effort estimation",
      "prompt_fragment": "When prioritizing tasks, use MoSCoW (Must/Should/Could/Won't)..."
    },
    "code-review": {
      "description": "Systematic code review checklist",
      "prompt_fragment": "When reviewing code: 1) Check correctness 2) Security 3) Performance..."
    }
  }
}
```

### Inter-Agent Communication
Agents can post messages to other running agents:
- ao.agent.message tool: send structured messages (question, handoff, status update)
- Messages queued if target agent isn't running, delivered on next run
- Enables EM to ask PO for requirement clarification, SWE to request code review, etc.

## Implementation Strategy
1. Extend agent profile schema in agent-runtime-config
2. Build tool access policy engine (pattern matching on MCP tool names)
3. Wire MCP server injection into agent-runner spawn flow
4. Add custom MCP server registration to project config
5. Define built-in personas (EM, PO, SWE)
6. Add skills/prompt fragment system
7. Add inter-agent messaging via shared MCP tool
8. Add CLI management commands
